get.description:
Get details of a specific API key.

Input: key_id in path
Auth: Bearer token required.

RETURNS: {key_id, name, permissions[], created_at, expires_at, last_used, is_active}
NOTE: Token value is NOT returned (only shown on creation).

RELATED ENDPOINTS BY INTENT:
- "Update this key" -> PUT /api-keys/{key_id}
- "Revoke this key" -> DELETE /api-keys/{key_id}
- "List all my keys" -> GET /api-keys/

put.description:
Update an API key's name, permissions, or status.

Input: {name?, permissions?, rate_limit?, is_active?}
Auth: Bearer token or API key required (must own key or be admin).

COMMON UPDATES:
- Rename: {name:"New Name"}
- Add permissions: {permissions:["api.read","api.write"]}
- Disable temporarily: {is_active:false}

RELATED ENDPOINTS BY INTENT:
- "Revoke key instead" -> DELETE /api-keys/{key_id}
- "Get current details" -> GET /api-keys/{key_id}
- "Create new key" -> POST /api-keys/

post.description:
Create a new team within an organization.

Input: {name, slug?, description?, permissions?}
Auth: Bearer token with teams.write permission required.

QUOTA: Subject to teams_per_org limit based on org tier.
Team members inherit team permissions automatically.

RELATED ENDPOINTS BY INTENT:
- "List org teams" -> GET /organizations/{org_id}/teams
- "Add member to team" -> POST /teams/{team_id}/members
- "Update team" -> PUT /teams/{team_id}
- "Delete team" -> DELETE /teams/{team_id}

get.description:
List users in an organization with optional filtering.

Input: ?role={admin|member}&limit={n}&next_token={token}
Auth: Bearer token with users.read permission required.

SCENARIOS:
1. All members: GET /organizations/{org_id}/users
2. Admins only: ?role=admin
3. Paginated: ?limit=20&next_token={from_previous}

RETURNS: [{user_id, email, name, role, joined_at}] or {users[], next_token}

RELATED ENDPOINTS BY INTENT:
- "Invite new user" -> POST /organizations/{org_id}/invite
- "Remove a user" -> DELETE /organizations/{org_id}/users/{user_id}
- "Change user's role" -> PUT /organizations/{org_id}/users/{user_id}
- "Get org details" -> GET /organizations/{org_id}

post.description:
Check if a user has a specific permission.

Input: {user_id, permission, org_id?, resource_type?, resource_id?}
Auth: Bearer token with users.read permission required.

SCENARIOS:
1. Basic check: {user_id, permission:"api.read"} -> {allowed:bool}
2. Org-scoped: {user_id, permission, org_id} -> checks within org context
3. Resource-level: {user_id, permission, resource_type, resource_id} -> fine-grained

RETURNS: {allowed:bool, reason?, source?, effective_permissions[]}

RELATED ENDPOINTS BY INTENT:
- "Grant this permission" -> POST /permissions/grant
- "Revoke this permission" -> POST /permissions/revoke
- "List all user permissions" -> GET /permissions/user/{user_id}

Revoke a permission from a user within an organization.

Input: ?user_id={user_id}&org_id={org_id}&permission={permission}
Auth: Bearer token with users.write permission required.

NOTE: Only revokes explicitly granted permissions, not role-inherited ones.

RELATED ENDPOINTS BY INTENT:
- "Grant a permission" -> POST /permissions/grant
- "Check if user has permission" -> POST /permissions/check
- "List user's current permissions" -> GET /permissions/user/{user_id}
- "Remove user from org entirely" -> DELETE /organizations/{org_id}/members/{user_id}
